# Command: polyp x1 y1 x2 y2 [... xn yn]
# Arguments: 
#    'x1' (int) x coordinate of the first point
#    'y1' (int) y coordinate of the first point
#    'x2' (int) x coordinate of the second point
#    'y2' (int) y coordinate of the second point
#    'xn, yn' (int) extra points that follow the path
# Description: Creates a closed line path from a sequence 
#              of points, where the last point will be 
#              connected to the first point
# Use example:
bounds 210 210 center invert_y
stroke 0.3;color 200 200 200;grid 200 200 10 10
color 0 0 0; stroke 1
# Example starts
polyp  4 85 25 77  52 56  83  46 34  86 54 62 64 91 
polyp 50 50 40 20 -40 20 -50 -40 76 -89
# Small example of filled line paths
colorf 90 32 32 32
polyp 0 0 80 20 100 -40
# There's no real need to align the numbers...
